Push-requires-clean-worktree enforcement locations (drained from AGENTS.md 2026-06-06): the rule (git push admissible only when git status --porcelain empty, AND the porcelain probe must be its own Bash tool-use event before the push, not &&-chained) is enforced at multiple layers: (1) lib/spool-dispatch.js::checkDispatchGates(sessionId,'git',{...}) runs the porcelain probe via spawnSync('git',['status','--porcelain']) and refuses dirty trees; (2) rs-plugkit gates.rs COMPLETE branch enforces the same invariant for transition-to-COMPLETE; (3) instruction prose in verify.rs + update_docs.rs restates it imperatively; (4) residual.rs skips the scan when dirty so the four-observation window cannot be claimed past an unwitnessed delta; (5) ccsniff --git-discipline flags post-hoc, scanning the last 20 Bash tool-use events (not shell commands inside them) for an explicit porcelain probe - add && commit && push in one Bash call = one event with no witness; ccsniff 1.1.8+ strips quoted commit-message bodies before regex match (true positives). Recall key: 'push clean worktree enforcement locations'.